author: talkSPORT
description: Arsene Wenger says he is unsure if Saturday's FA Cup final will be his last game as Arsenal boss. The Frenchman insists he will remain in management next season, but has refused to confirm whether that will be with the north London club. Wenger, who has faced protests from fans calling for him to go, is out of contract in the summer and will discuss his future at a board meeting following the Wembley clash with Chelsea. When asked if it will be his last match as Arsenal manager, he replied: "I don't know.
title: Arsene Wenger says FA Cup final will not be his last game in football - but could be last as Arsenal boss
